              }
            ]
          },
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 24,
          "padding": [
            60,
            120,
            80,
            120
          ],
          "alignItems": "center",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "wqLku",
              "fill": "$accent-gold",
              "content": "DYNAMIC TARGETS",
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 11,
              "fontWeight": "700",
              "letterSpacing": 3
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "Yiutx",
              "fill": "$text-primary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": 900,
              "content": "Targets that move with you —\ntapers, bonuses, and daily adaptation",
              "textAlign": "center",
              "fontFamily": "Sora",
              "fontSize": 48,
              "fontWeight": "bold",
              "letterSpacing": -1.5
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "tz50C",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": 720,
              "content": "Static targets assume your life never changes. NutriKit's targets can taper over time, respond to your workouts, and adjust day by day — so your nutrition plan keeps pace with your actual goals.",
              "lineHeight": 1.6,
              "textAlign": "center",
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 18,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "y6X2D",
          "name": "Article Body",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 48,
          "padding": [
            0,
            340
          ],
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "CFq3p",
              "name": "Section - Tapered Targets",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 20,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "HCgcR",
                  "fill": "$text-primary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Tapered Targets",
                  "fontFamily": "Sora",
                  "fontSize": 32,
                  "fontWeight": "bold",
                  "letterSpacing": -0.5
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "JUlPr",
                  "fill": "$text-secondary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "A taper lets you smoothly transition any nutrient target from one value to another over a period of time. Instead of abruptly switching from 250g carbs to 150g carbs, you define a start value, an end value, and a duration — and NutriKit interpolates your daily target across that window.\n\nThis is how competitive athletes periodize their nutrition. It's how people gradually reduce calories during a cut. And it's how you can slowly increase protein intake without shocking your digestive system or your grocery budget.\n\nHere's how it works mechanically:",
                  "lineHeight": 1.7,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "AOJzM",
              "name": "Section - Setup",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 16,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "8eVzc",
                  "fill": "$accent-gold",
                  "content": "Setting up a taper",
                  "fontFamily": "Sora",
                  "fontSize": 24,
                  "fontWeight": "bold"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "FBxWa",
                  "fill": "$text-secondary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "For any nutrient, you can create a taper by specifying:\n\n1. Start value — where you are now (or any custom starting point)\n2. End value — where you want to be\n3. Start date — when the taper begins (defaults to today)\n4. Duration — how many days the taper runs\n5. Curve shape — how the interpolation behaves between start and end\n\nOnce active, your daily target is automatically calculated based on where you are in the taper timeline. You don't have to think about it — just log your food and NutriKit tells you today's number.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.7,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "6QAc1",
              "name": "Section - Curves",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 20,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "Ab9Vq",
                  "fill": "$accent-gold",
                  "content": "Curve shapes explained",
                  "fontFamily": "Sora",
                  "fontSize": 24,
                  "fontWeight": "bold"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "6cRqR",
                  "fill": "$text-secondary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "The curve shape determines how the interpolation progresses between your start and end values. NutriKit offers four options:\n\n• Linear — a straight line from start to end. Equal change every day. Simple and predictable. Best for moderate tapers where you don't need front-loading or back-loading.\n\n• Stepped — the taper divides into equal-length steps (e.g., weekly blocks). Your target drops at the start of each step and stays flat within it. This mimics how many coaches program nutrition phases — weekly targets rather than daily drift.\n\n• Ease-in — changes slowly at first, then accelerates toward the end. Useful when you want to ease into a taper gently and make the bigger adjustments later, once you've adapted.\n\n• Ease-out — changes quickly at first, then decelerates. Useful when you want to make the big move early and fine-tune toward the end.\n\nAll four curves arrive at the same end value on the same date. The difference is the path taken.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.7,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "bt8Ks",
