            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "vTnGn",
              "name": "Section - Managing Tapers",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 20,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "2iQoE",
                  "fill": "$accent-gold",
                  "content": "Managing active tapers",
                  "fontFamily": "Sora",
                  "fontSize": 24,
                  "fontWeight": "bold"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "49M4k",
                  "fill": "$text-secondary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Once a taper is running, you're not locked in. You can:\n\n• Pause the taper — freezes your current interpolated value. The taper resumes from where it left off when you unpause.\n• Adjust the end value or duration mid-taper — the remaining days recalculate smoothly from today's value to the new end.\n• Override a single day — if you need a different target for just today (e.g., a rest day during a carb taper), you can set a manual override without disrupting the taper.\n• Cancel the taper — your target reverts to whatever it would be without the taper (either the smart calculated value or a manual override).\n\nMultiple nutrients can have independent tapers running simultaneously. You might taper carbs down over 6 weeks while simultaneously tapering protein up over 4 weeks.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.7,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "8jvJJ",
              "name": "Section - Workout Bonuses",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 20,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "bZzzU",
                  "fill": "$text-primary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Workout Bonuses",
                  "fontFamily": "Sora",
                  "fontSize": 32,
                  "fontWeight": "bold",
                  "letterSpacing": -0.5
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "tT8Dh",
                  "fill": "$text-secondary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "On days you exercise, your nutritional needs change. You burn more energy, you break down more muscle protein, and you deplete more glycogen. NutriKit's workout bonuses let your targets respond to this automatically.\n\nWhen Apple Health reports active energy burned from a workout, NutriKit can increase your protein and carbohydrate targets for that day. The bonus is applied in real time — as your workout data syncs, your targets update.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.7,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "kAeqG",
              "name": "Section - Adaptive vs Fixed",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 16,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "xrmIk",
                  "fill": "$accent-gold",
                  "content": "Adaptive vs. fixed bonuses",
                  "fontFamily": "Sora",
                  "fontSize": 24,
                  "fontWeight": "bold"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "3bpyM",
                  "fill": "$text-secondary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "NutriKit offers two bonus modes:\n\nAdaptive bonuses scale with how much you burned. You configure a bonus per 100 kcal of active energy. For example, +5g protein per 100 kcal burned means a 400 kcal workout adds 20g to your protein target. A 200 kcal workout adds 10g. The bonus is proportional to the effort.\n\nFixed bonuses add a flat amount regardless of workout intensity. If you set +30g carbs as a fixed bonus, any workout day gets +30g — whether you did a 20-minute walk or a 90-minute lifting session.\n\nAdaptive is better for people with variable workout intensities. Fixed is simpler and works well when your workouts are consistent.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.7,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "jOBpx",
              "name": "Section - Eating Windows",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 16,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "bkK9c",
                  "fill": "$accent-gold",
                  "content": "Eating windows around workouts",
                  "fontFamily": "Sora",
                  "fontSize": 24,
                  "fontWeight": "bold"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "UDg0Y",
                  "fill": "$text-secondary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Workout bonuses can be configured with an optional eating window. This means the bonus only applies to meals logged within a certain time range around your workout — for example, 1 hour before to 3 hours after.\n\nThis supports peri-workout nutrition strategies where you want to concentrate extra protein and carbs around training, rather than spreading the bonus across the whole day. If no eating window is set, the bonus applies to your full-day target.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.7,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "A7lYa",
              "name": "Section - Stacking",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 20,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "Z3zQa",
                  "fill": "$text-primary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "How it all stacks together",
                  "fontFamily": "Sora",
                  "fontSize": 32,
                  "fontWeight": "bold",
                  "letterSpacing": -0.5
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "47yMv",
                  "fill": "$text-secondary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Tapers and workout bonuses aren't mutually exclusive — they compose. Here's the order of operations for any given nutrient on any given day:\n\n1. Start with the base target — either the Smart Target (calculated from your profile) or a manual override\n2. If a taper is active, the base target is replaced by the interpolated taper value for today\n3. If a workout bonus is configured and you've burned active energy today, the bonus is added on top\n\nThis means you can run a 6-week carb taper from 300g to 200g, and on workout days within that taper, your carbs still get a bump. The system is composable by design.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.7,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
