              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 11,
              "fontWeight": "700",
              "letterSpacing": 3
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "LGHt1",
              "fill": "$text-primary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": 900,
              "content": "Liquid glass stickers that make\nyour nutrition look beautiful",
              "textAlign": "center",
              "fontFamily": "Sora",
              "fontSize": 48,
              "fontWeight": "bold",
              "letterSpacing": -1.5
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "79UqI",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": 720,
              "content": "NutriKit generates stunning translucent stickers showing your meal or daily nutrition breakdown — calories, macros, and foods with emoji. Place them on your photos or videos and share anywhere.",
              "lineHeight": 1.6,
              "textAlign": "center",
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 18,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "xnJTy",
          "name": "Article Body",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 48,
          "padding": [
            0,
            340
          ],
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "4nL92",
              "name": "Section - What Are Stickers",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 20,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "B75ik",
                  "fill": "$text-primary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "What are meal stickers?",
                  "fontFamily": "Sora",
                  "fontSize": 32,
                  "fontWeight": "bold",
                  "letterSpacing": -0.5
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "tWWhc",
                  "fill": "$text-secondary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Meal stickers are translucent, glass-effect overlays that display your nutrition data in a visually striking format. They're designed to look beautiful on top of food photos — like a premium UI widget floating over your meal.\n\nEach sticker shows:\n\n• Total calories for the meal (or the full day)\n• Macro breakdown — protein, carbs, and fat in grams\n• A list of foods you ate, each with an auto-assigned emoji\n• The meal name and date\n\nThe glass effect uses blur and transparency to blend naturally with whatever photo or background it's placed on. It's not a flat graphic pasted on top — it genuinely looks like a frosted glass panel hovering over your content.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.7,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "f7e1U",
              "name": "Section - Types",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 20,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "M5pPE",
                  "fill": "$text-primary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Sticker types",
                  "fontFamily": "Sora",
                  "fontSize": 32,
                  "fontWeight": "bold",
                  "letterSpacing": -0.5
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "qRXo7",
                  "fill": "$text-secondary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "NutriKit offers two sticker modes:\n\nMeal stickers show data for a single meal — what you ate at lunch, for example. These are perfect for Instagram stories or messages to friends showing what you had.\n\nDaily stickers show your full-day nutrition summary — all meals combined, total macros, and a complete food list. These work well for end-of-day recaps and accountability posts.\n\nBoth types are generated instantly from your diary data. There's nothing to configure or design — NutriKit composes the sticker automatically from what you've already logged.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.7,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "hIPHv",
              "name": "Section - Sharing",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 20,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "CFC0W",
                  "fill": "$text-primary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Sharing and placement",
                  "fontFamily": "Sora",
                  "fontSize": 32,
                  "fontWeight": "bold",
                  "letterSpacing": -0.5
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "1skGQ",
                  "fill": "$text-secondary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Once generated, stickers can be:\n\n• Placed on a photo from your camera roll — drag and resize the sticker over your food photo, then export the combined image\n• Shared directly to Instagram Stories, where the sticker appears as a draggable overlay\n• Copied to clipboard and pasted into any app — iMessage, WhatsApp, social media\n• Saved as a standalone transparent PNG for use anywhere\n\nThe sticker is rendered at high resolution with transparency, so it works on any background — light, dark, or busy. The glass effect adapts to the underlying content, always remaining readable.\n\nThis feature exists because sharing is a natural part of the nutrition tracking experience. People share their meals, their progress, and their daily logs. NutriKit makes that sharing look effortless and professional.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.7,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
